race.comment: POETIC STORM (4) has hit the line powerfully to pick up a runner-up cheque at both outings this prep, the latest here at this trip in a BM56. Tackles a better race today but strips fitter and gets all the favours from an inside draw. SISTINE TUNNEL (3) came from a long way back to just nail POETIC STORM here at this distance recently. Drawn under the arches but will get back and be putting in the big ones late. STARMAE (1) raced handy then battled on gamely but found one a touch better over 1300m at Swan Hill last start. Racing well and dropping back to 1200m is a tick. GO LEFT (13) travelled up on the speed then showed great fighting qualities to score on debut over 1100m at Tatura recently. Harder here but has great scope for improvement. ZENACITY (7) has placed two from three when fresh so is worth considering off a six-month break.
